From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: eng33 <eng33@luckfox.com>
Date: Tue, 30 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] shared/shell: fix wordexp flags – use WRDE_NOCMD not WRDE_APPEND

WRDE_APPEND is not meaningful in the wordexp() call in cmd_exec(); the
intent is to suppress command substitution (WRDE_NOCMD).  This matches
the fix carried downstream in the Luckfox Buildroot patch set.

Signed-off-by: eng33 <eng33@luckfox.com>
---
 src/shared/shell.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/shared/shell.c b/src/shared/shell.c
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/src/shared/shell.c
+++ b/src/shared/shell.c
@@ -1,6 +1,6 @@
 	int flags = WRDE_SHOWERR;
-	flags |= WRDE_APPEND;
+	flags |= WRDE_NOCMD;
 	if (wordexp(args, &w, flags) < 0)
